article.headline: Long Beach St. 60, UC Davis 56
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- Eugene Phelps snagged a double-double, scoring 15 points and pulling down 15 rebounds, as Long Beach State held off UC Davis 60-56 on Wednesday night. The 49ers (10-8, 5-0 Big West) took their largest lead of the game, 50-35, midway through the second half after scoring 14 unanswered points. But the Aggies (6-11, 1-5) rallied in the final eight minutes, outscoring Long Beach State 21-10 and pulling within two points on a 3-pointer by Ryan Sypkens with 25 seconds to go. But it was a close as UC Davis got. Joe Harden led the Aggies with a game-high 20 points while Sypkens scored 16 and Eddie Miller 10. Larry Anderson and Casper Ware each scored 12 points for the 49ers and Greg Plater added 11.
